<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="28" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d28">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/1166</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Assistant Secretary of State</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PW1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the French
                                    Ambassador</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_JJJ1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Jusserand</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-26">
                                        <hi rend="italic">January 26, 1918</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Ambassador</hi>: Referring to the
                                inquiry which Mr. <persName>Sartiges</persName> of your Embassy
                                telephoned to my office a few days ago, regarding the interpretation
                                of item number 10 in the peace program outlined by the President in
                                his address to Congress on January 8, I hasten to confirm the
                                telephone message with Mr. <persName>Sartiges</persName> this
                                morning to the effect that the President has replied to an inquiry
                                submitted to him that the statement meant “that we wish the place of
                                the <hi rend="italic">peoples</hi> of Austria-Hungary safeguarded
                                and assured.”</p>
                            <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_PW1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William Phillips</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>